15#ifndef DNS_ORDER_H
16#define DNS_ORDER_H 1
17
18/*! \file dns/order.h */
19
20#include <isc/lang.h>
21#include <isc/types.h>
22
23#include <dns/types.h>
24
25ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
26
27isc_result_t
28dns_order_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_order_t **orderp);
29/*%<
30 * Create a order object.
31 *
32 * Requires:
33 * \li 'orderp' to be non NULL and '*orderp == NULL'.
34 *\li 'mctx' to be valid.
35 *
36 * Returns:
37 *\li ISC_R_SUCCESS
38 *\li ISC_R_NOMEMORY
39 */
40
41isc_result_t
42dns_order_add(dns_order_t *order, const dns_name_t *name,
43 dns_rdatatype_t rdtype, dns_rdataclass_t rdclass,
44 unsigned int mode);
45/*%<
46 * Add a entry to the end of the order list.
47 *
48 * Requires:
49 * \li 'order' to be valid.
50 *\li 'name' to be valid.
51 *\li 'mode' to be one of #DNS_RDATASETATTR_RANDOMIZE,
52 * #DNS_RDATASETATTR_FIXEDORDER or zero (#DNS_RDATASETATTR_CYCLIC).
53 *
54 * Returns:
55 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
56 *\li #ISC_R_NOMEMORY
57 */
58
59unsigned int
60dns_order_find(dns_order_t *order, const dns_name_t *name,
61 dns_rdatatype_t rdtype, dns_rdataclass_t rdclass);
62/*%<
63 * Find the first matching entry on the list.
64 *
65 * Requires:
66 *\li 'order' to be valid.
67 *\li 'name' to be valid.
68 *
69 * Returns the mode set by dns_order_add() or zero.
70 */
71
72void
73dns_order_attach(dns_order_t *source, dns_order_t **target);
74/*%<
75 * Attach to the 'source' object.
76 *
77 * Requires:
78 * \li 'source' to be valid.
79 *\li 'target' to be non NULL and '*target == NULL'.
80 */
81
82void
83dns_order_detach(dns_order_t **orderp);
84/*%<
85 * Detach from the object. Clean up if last this was the last
86 * reference.
87 *
88 * Requires:
89 *\li '*orderp' to be valid.
90 */
91
92ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
93
94#endif /* DNS_ORDER_H */
95
